# Cursor Rules for AI Coding Assistant

## Linting Requirements
- Run `read_lints` tool only when committing changes to git or when specifically requested
- Fix any linting errors before finalizing the commit
- Check linting for all modified files before git commits

## Code Quality Standards
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow Next.js best practices
- Maintain consistent code formatting
- Use proper React patterns and hooks

## File Organization
- Keep components in `/src/components/`
- Use proper import/export patterns
- Maintain consistent naming conventions

## Testing
- Always verify changes work in the browser
- Check for console errors
- Ensure responsive design works properly
